GIT:  (version control)
  Git is a tool, save and , manage different version of your files and code.

version control means track changes, recover previous saved code.

Git Config: 
  git config : git know who you are, like set username or email 

  1.System level → affects all users on this computer.
  2.Global level → affects only your user.
  3.Local level → affects only the current repository.

System Level:
sudo: (super-user do)
1. create system level settings: (file created)
    sudo touch /etc/gitconfig   
2. Add a system-level username and email
    sudo git config --system user.name "System User"
    sudo git config --system user.email "system@example.com"
3. Verify system-level config
    git config --system --list



